ly be called a republican hero: each contributes to the promotion or protection or provision of republican values. Each exemplifies the heroic virtues of their age. However, taken conjunctively, each contributes to what Lusztig conceives as the complete republican hero of the modern age.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aHeroes in literature. 0aHeroesxPolitical aspects. 0aRepublicanism. 4aCultural Studies : Popular Culture. 4aHistory : History. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Leadership Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849538540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438495385423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438495385/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles